HEADWORD: Octocerata
<hw>Oc`to*cer"a*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'oktw`</grk> eight + <?/, a horn.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A suborder of <class>Cephalopoda</class> including
<gen>Octopus</gen>, <gen>Argonauta</gen>, and allied genera, having
eight arms around the head; -- called also
<altname>Octopoda</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Octochord</ent>⟦br⟧
